{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770051163,"nonce":"aGyGCT3or0Ti4Lu1C/qs4R4M928=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nrop4","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/129","origin":"github"},"title":"[Agent UX] Format GitHub references as clickable links","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen agents report on GitHub issues and pull requests, they should present them in a format that users can click to open in their browser. This applies to both CLI and IDE environments.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\nAgents currently report issues/PRs like:\n- \"Issue #22 - Setup Test Infrastructure\"\n- \"PR #34 is open with 10 review comments\"\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\nAgents should format GitHub references as clickable links:\n- Use full URLs: `https://github.com/owner/repo/issues/22`\n- Use markdown links where supported: `[#22](https://github.com/owner/repo/issues/22)`\n- Include the title for context: `[Issue #22: Setup Test Infrastructure](https://github.com/owner/repo/issues/22)`\n\n## Examples\n\n**Bad:**\n```\nIssue #34 has unresolved review comments\n```\n\n**Good:**\n```\n[Issue #34: Add test infrastructure](https://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/pull/34) has unresolved review comments\n```\n\n**Good (plain URL for CLI):**\n```\nIssue #34 has unresolved review comments\nhttps://github.com/rolker/unh_marine_autonomy/pull/34\n```\n\n## Scope\n\nThis should apply to:\n- ✅ Issue references\n- ✅ Pull request references\n- ✅ Commit references (use short SHA with link to full commit)\n- ✅ Repository references\n- ✅ Both when analyzing GitHub repos AND when reporting on local workspace issues\n\n## Implementation\n\nAdd this guidance to agent instruction files:\n- `.agent/AI_RULES.md` - Core rule about GitHub reference formatting\n- `.agent/CLI_COMMANDS.md` - Examples in command outputs\n- `.github/copilot-instructions.md` - For Copilot-specific agents\n\n## Priority\n\nMedium - Improves UX but doesn't block functionality\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: Copilot CLI Agent (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}